@startuml
' @id(DOM-BRIEF)
' @id(DOM-PLAN-SCOPE)
' @desc(DOM-BRIEF, "The .mdd/docs/brief.md alignment artifact: objective/outcome, in-scope, out-of-scope/non-goals, ADR-lite architecture decisions, best-practice tooling choices, and NFRs. Signed off by the developer before any model or PLAN is produced; it is the description /mdd-generate consumes.")
' @desc(DOM-PLAN-SCOPE, "A .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md item parsed from the priority-ordered checklist. Model-bearing items carry an inline @scope(<id>,…) naming the objective @ids they realize (Ralph routes them to a realize-slice cycle); infra/tooling items carry none (general tools). Every @scope id must resolve to an objective @id, and the union of all @scope ids must cover every implementation-bearing objective @id, so RALPH-DONE coincides with whole-model parity.")
' Objective-side domain for the greenfield kickoff (cycle 0027).
title Greenfield kickoff domain (objective)

class Brief {
  + objective : String
  + inScope : List<String>
  + outOfScope : List<String>
  + decisions : List<AdrEntry>
  + tooling : List<String>
  + nfrs : List<String>
  + signedOff : Boolean
}

class AdrEntry {
  + context : String
  + decision : String
  + rationale : String
  + alternatives : String
}

class PlanItem {
  + text : String
  + done : Boolean
  + scope : List<Id>
  + isInfra() : Boolean
}

Brief "1" o-- "*" AdrEntry : records >

note bottom of Brief
  Signed off before any model is generated
  (OCL-KICKOFF-BRIEF-SIGNED-OFF). The description
  /mdd-generate consumes.
end note

note bottom of PlanItem
  isInfra() is true exactly when scope is empty.
  Every scope id resolves to an objective @id
  (OCL-KICKOFF-SCOPE-IDS-EXIST); the union of all
  items' scope covers every implementation-bearing
  objective @id (OCL-KICKOFF-PLAN-COVERS-OBJECTIVE),
  so exhausting the PLAN equals whole-model parity.
end note
@enduml
